Name: spellCheck

Type: property

Syntax: set the spellCheck of <field> to {true | false}

Summary:
Specifies whether misspelled words in a <field> are underlined with a
red squiggly line.

Associations: field

Introduced: 1.0.0

OS: mac, windows

Platforms: desktop

Example:
set the spellCheck of field "body" to true

Example:
set the spellCheck of the focusedObject to false

Value (bool):
The <spellCheck> of a <field(keyword)> is true or false.
By default, the <spellCheck> <property> of newly created
<field(object)|fields> is set to false.

Description:
Use the <spellCheck> <property> to enable inline spell checking for a
<field(keyword)>. When enabled, misspelled words are underlined with a
red squiggly line as the user types or whenever the field's text
changes.

When <spellCheck> is set to true, the engine passes the full plain-text
content of the field to the system spell checker. Each word identified
as misspelled is marked with a red zigzag underline drawn one pixel
below the text baseline. The underline updates automatically whenever
the text of the field changes.

When <spellCheck> is set to false, all spelling error indicators are
removed immediately and no further spell checking is performed on that
field.

Spell checking uses the system dictionary and respects the user's
language settings. On macOS the system spell checker is
`NSSpellChecker`. On Windows 8 and later the system spell checker is
the `ISpellChecker` COM API (Windows Spell Checking API). On other
platforms the <spellCheck> property is accepted without error but has
no visible effect.

>*Note:* The <spellCheck> property performs checking only — it does not
> provide suggestions or auto-correction. To control whether the system
> offers auto-corrections while the user is typing, see the
> `allowInlineInput` property.

References: lockText (property), sharedText (property),
allowInlineInput (property), field (keyword), field (object)

Tags: ui
